      "BSEE onsite investigation conducted April 23, 2018"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 16, 2018 at approximately 1145 hours, a crane mechanic helper injured his right knee while attempting to store a six foot ladder. The CMH stepped off a five inch drop that was painted red on the front but had no markings on top to indicate the uneven surface. He fell and his right knee contacted the grating, initially causing a bruise. After three days of continuous discomfort and swelling, medical examination revealed a fractured knee cap.",
    "recommendations": [
      "The BSEE Lafayette District office makes no recommendations to the Regional Office of Incident Investigations"
    ],
